      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "IMINASTATE (4) no match for Tron Bolt two-back from a wide gate, then chipped away late to secure third in a small field over 1400m at Rosehill. Hard fit now and can race a little closer from the low gate. Solid top-three contender. DIVINE OFFERING (2) returned a solid set of figures on debut when he came from near last on the turn to finish third over 1250m at Canterbury. Will benefit from that experience and shouldn't be a Maiden for long. STREET JEWEL (8) showed good early gate speed on debut before tiring to run fifth over 1100m at Gosford. Will hold a forward position today and expected to go close. ULTIMATE WARRIOR (5) given every chance on debut from the inside gate before tiring to run seventh over 1250m at Canterbury. Tricky map today and likely to go back and be ridden for luck. Place best.",
